1 Combine the berries and sugar in a medium saucepan over low heat. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. 2 Cook the berries and sugar for about 5 minutes, allowing them to boil very gently, or until they are slightly thickened. 3 Cool the mixture and puree it in a blender. Strain the sauce into a bowl to remove the seeds. 4 Stir in the lemon juice and Kirsch. Pass the sauce in a sauceboat or bowl. Keep the sauce covered and refrigerated before and after use.